itemDescription: son of George Sutherland-Leveson-Gower, 3rd Duke of Sutherland

wikipedia_page.main: Cromartie Sutherland-Leveson-Gower, 4th Duke of Sutherland,  (20 July 1851– 27 June 1913), styled Lord Cromartie Sutherland-Leveson-Gower until 1858, Earl Gower between 1858 and 1861 and Marquess of Stafford between 1861 and 1892, was a British peer and politician from the Leveson-Gower family.
